# MentionMe Base Mini App - Development Rules

## Documentation Access
- Base Mini App documentation is in /docs folder
- Reference these files when implementing features:
  - Authentication: docs/Authentication_Documentation.docx
  - Payments: docs/Accept_Payment_Documentation.docx
  - Navigation: docs/Navigation_documentation.docx
  - Context: docs/Context_Documentation.docx
  - Base Account: docs/Base_Account_Documentation.docx
  - Mini App Setup: docs/Minikit_Documentation.docx
- When unsure about Base SDK usage, read relevant doc file first

## Critical Navigation Rules
- NEVER use <a href=""> tags for external links (crashes WebView)
- ALWAYS use: sdk.actions.openUrl(url) from @farcaster/miniapp-sdk
- For cast sharing: sdk.actions.composeCast({ text, embeds })
- For viewing casts: sdk.actions.viewCast(castUrl)

## Authentication & Security
- User is already connected via Base Account - NO wallet connection UI
- For auth: use sdk.quickAuth.getToken()
- Verify JWT on backend with @farcaster/quick-auth
- sdk.context data is NOT secure - only use for UX hints

## Payment Integration
- Use pay() from @base-org/account for all payments
- Currency: USDC only
- Cannot collect: email, phone, shipping address (not supported in Mini Apps)
- Platform fee: 10% of every transaction
- Recipient gets: 90% of payment

## Code Quality Standards
- Explain changes BEFORE making them
- Only modify files that need changing
- Keep implementations simple
- Add loading states for all async operations
- Handle all errors with user-friendly messages
- Use TypeScript strict mode

## Project Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 14 with App Router
- Language: TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Mini App SDK: @farcaster/miniapp-sdk
- Payments: @base-org/account
- Wallet: Wagmi + farcasterMiniApp() connector
